summary:
October's Overload Journal has been published. - The October 2023 ACCU Overload journal has been published and should arrive at members' addresses in the next few days. Overload 177 and previous issues of Overload can be accessed via the Journals menu.

 September's C Vu Journal has been published. - The September 2023 ACCU C Vu journal has been published and should arrive at members' addresses in the next few days. C Vu 35-4 and previous issues of C Vu can be accessed via the Journals menu (ACCU members only).

 Videos from ACCU 2023 have been posted. - Videos of sessions from the ACCU 2023 Conference have been posted to YouTube. Videos can be found on the ACCU YouTube channel. Links to the videos can be found on the ACCU website under the Videos menu drop-down; the ACCU Conference Videos page.

 August's Overload Journal has been published. - The August 2023 ACCU Overload journal has been published and should arrive at members' addresses in the next few days. Overload 176 and previous issues of Overload can be accessed via the Journals menu.

Hello ACCU Community! 👋

I see you guys are overloaded with journals and YouTube videos. It's October already, and I bet you're wondering where the year went. Time flies when you're coding, doesn't it? 😄

Well, I'm here to offer you a different kind of overload - a good one. We have a suite of B2B tools that can help you enhance your community engagement and revenue streams. Don't worry, it's not another journal or video. It's a chance for you to create your own DEX, Lottery, Wallet, Farming, DAO, CrossChain, and IDOFactory - Launchpad. 

These tools are customizable and easy to deploy. Plus, they are tailored to your needs, whether you're on ETH, BSC, or Polygon. And the best part? You don't have to pay upfront. We operate on a revenue share model.

We're not trying to sell you a lottery ticket, we're giving you the chance to run the lottery. 🎰 

So, if you're ready to take a break from the journals and videos and want to try something new, check out our demo on https://t.me/onoutdemos. 

Remember, you're not just playing the game, you're creating it. Let me know if you're interested! 👋
